    "NLTK's NER is based on a supervised machine learning algorithm (Maximum Entropy Classifier), and it is trained on the ACE corpus.",
    "The output entities include PERSON, LOCATION, ORGANISATION [83].",
    "OpenNLP 67 is a machine learning-based toolkit (developed with Java) for the processing of natural language text.",
    "It supports the most common NLP tasks, including named entity recognition (NER) [16].",
    "FINET 68 [41] is a FGNER system handling short text (such as tweets or sentences)."
